简直和狮子吃豆泥一样荒唐

437
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:37,048
- That doesn't make any sense.  - I know it doesn't make any sense.
- 没道理  - 的确没道理

438
00:23:37,049 --> 00:23:39,684
You seriously have a problem with me not drinking, after what happened?
发生了那样的事 你还计较我不喝酒?

439
00:23:39,685 --> 00:23:42,320
- I don't, but King Arthur does!  - Oh, this'll be good.
- 我不知道 不过亚瑟王知道!  - 噢 没准有点用

440
00:23:42,321 --> 00:23:43,823
What's King Arthur got to do with it?
亚瑟王会怎么做?

441
00:23:43,923 --> 00:23:47,234
Do you honestly think that King Arthur came back from the Battle of Hastings,
从黑斯廷斯战场归来后 你觉得亚瑟王

442
00:23:47,393 --> 00:23:50,795
- fucking rocked up at Arthur's Castle...  - Camelot.
- 会他妈躲进城堡...  - 卡米洛特

443
00:23:50,796 --> 00:23:52,063
walked up to the bar and went,
走向酒吧然后说

444
00:23:52,064 --> 00:23:53,998
"Hello. Could I have a tap water?"
"你好 给我来杯自来水?"

445
00:23:53,999 --> 00:23:56,502
No, because they didn't have running water in Arthurian times.
不会 在亚瑟王的时代 根本就没有自来水

446
00:23:56,835 --> 00:24:00,505
Exactly. He would have had a mead. The King Arthur of beers.
说的没错 他会要杯蜂蜜酒 亚瑟王的啤酒

447
00:24:00,506 --> 00:24:02,679
And I'm less of a man because I choose to drink water?
我喝水就不是男人了吗?

448
00:24:02,908 --> 00:24:04,375
Well, it's a bit "ooh ducky", innit?
的确有点娘 不是吗?

449
00:24:04,376 --> 00:24:05,743
That's not very PC, Gary.
加里 这么说很不友好

450
00:24:05,744 --> 00:24:07,645
Get out of the '90s, Pete.
别整老一套 皮特

451
00:24:07,646 --> 00:24:10,648
There's nothing "ooh ducky" about being teetotal,
戒酒一点也不娘

452
00:24:10,649 --> 00:24:13,184
about walking into a pub after a rugby match
尤其是在橄榄球赛结束后 走进酒吧

453
00:24:13,185 --> 00:24:17,655
and ordering a tap water at a bar packed full of big ugly bastards wearing warpaint.
往脸上涂着油彩混球们中间一站 然后要一杯白开水

454
00:24:17,656 --> 00:24:20,892
That, my friend, takes confidence, yeah? I'm talking balls
那可是需要极大自信的 朋友 我有的是胆量

455
00:24:20,893 --> 00:24:22,566
You said it, poof.
谁信啊 傻瓜

456
00:24:23,195 --> 00:24:27,234
I don't know if you're aware of this, Gary, but we are not teenagers anymore.
我不知道你意识到没有 加里 我们已经不是小孩子了

457
00:24:27,366 --> 00:24:29,867
And God forbid you ever have children, because if...
上帝是不会允许你有孩子的 因为...

458
00:24:29,868 --> 00:24:31,035
I might have kids.
我可能有孩子

459
00:24:31,036 --> 00:24:32,538
Then you had better be ready to take responsibility...
那你最好做好负责任的准备...

460
00:24:32,638 --> 00:24:34,242
No. I mean I might have kids.
不 我是说我可能真有孩子

461
00:24:34,873 --> 00:24:37,786
You remember Karen Eggerton, who I fucked?
还记得卡伦・艾格顿吗 我们睡过?

462
00:24:38,210 --> 00:24:40,713
She was two weeks late when her parents emigrated to Normandy.
他们家移民去诺曼底的时候 她月经迟到了两周

463
00:24:40,879 --> 00:24:44,554
I never heard from her again. She might have had a baby.
我和她再也没联系过了 她也许有孩子了

464
00:24:44,750 --> 00:24:47,230
