00:43:11,589 --> 00:43:12,989
- To London?  - To The Trusty Servant.
- 去伦敦?  - 去忠仆

791
00:43:12,990 --> 00:43:15,163
- Are you fucking kidding?  - Oh, yeah.
- 你搞笑吧?  - 哦 我错了

792
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:18,528
It's The Good Companions next. I always mix those two up.
下场是去好伙伴 我总是把这两个搞混

793
00:43:18,529 --> 00:43:20,363
Are you saying we move on to the next pub?
你提议我们去下个酒吧?

794
00:43:20,364 --> 00:43:22,401
We should get in The Beast and head back to London!
我们应该开上野兽 然后直奔伦敦

795
00:43:22,533 --> 00:43:24,877
- My brake light is broken.  - So don't use the brakes!
- 我刹车灯坏了  - 那就别刹车啊!

796
00:43:25,002 --> 00:43:27,070
- I'm way over the limit.  - When has that ever stopped you?
- 我早就醉酒了  - 你之前醉酒不也照开的吗?

797
00:43:27,071 --> 00:43:29,847
I don't want to put any more points on Pete's license.
我不想再让皮特的驾照扣分了

798
00:43:29,974 --> 00:43:32,509
Andy can drive, he's teetotal!
安迪能开 他滴酒未沾!

799
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:45,088
Ah!
啊!

800
00:43:45,089 --> 00:43:46,490
That's settles it then.
那就这么定了

801
00:43:46,491 --> 00:43:48,692
The last thing we need to do is get pulled over by the police.
我们最不希望的 就是被警察拦住

802
00:43:48,693 --> 00:43:49,993
A, we're all drunk,
首先 我们都喝酒了

803
00:43:49,994 --> 00:43:52,863
B, they might be in on it and, C, we've got blood on our hands.
其次 他们可能被调包 最后 我们手上都是血

804
00:43:52,864 --> 00:43:55,065
- It's more like ink.  - We've got ink on our hands.
- 更像是墨水  - 我们手上都是墨水

805
00:43:55,066 --> 00:43:58,835
- So, has it got messy yet?  - What?
- 那么 看起来还没造成什么乱子嘛?  - 什么?

806
00:43:58,836 --> 00:44:01,817
- What are you, five pubs in?  - Four.
- 怎么样 逛了五家了?  - 才四家

807
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:05,687
Oh, not even halfway. Plenty more fun to be had.
哦 还没过一半啊 接下去乐子好多着呢

808
00:44:06,944 --> 00:44:08,355
Enjoy your night, Peter.
玩的开心啊 皮特

809
00:44:08,479 --> 00:44:09,549
Thank you.
多谢

810
00:44:11,282 --> 00:44:12,556
Thank you.
谢谢

811
00:44:16,053 --> 00:44:17,087
Sorry.
不好意思

812
00:44:17,088 --> 00:44:19,322
The way I see it, we've told everybody we were doing The Golden Mile.
我觉得 我们跟所有人都说过了我们在豪饮马拉松

813
00:44:19,323 --> 00:44:20,390
You did.
只有你说了

814
00:44:20,391 --> 00:44:22,159
If we suddenly jump in The Beast now and head for the hills,
如果我们突然跳上野兽 回头走人的话

815
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:23,493
they're gonna know that we know,
他们就知道 我们知道了

816
00:44:23,494 --> 00:44:25,729
but if we keep doing what we're doing and going where we're going,
但是如果我们继续按照预定计划的话

817
00:44:25,730 --> 00:44:26,796
then they're not gonna know.
他们就不会知道了

818
00:44:26,797 --> 00:44:27,998
- Know what?  - That we know.
- 知道什么?  - 我们知道的事情

819
00:44:27,999 --> 00:44:30,502
I suggest we finish what we started and leave quietly in the morning.
我建议 我们把事情办完 然后明早安静地离开

820
00:44:30,635 --> 00:44:33,878
- Wait. You're really suggesting...  - We finish The Golden Mile.
- 等等 那你是建议...  - 我们继续完成豪饮马拉松

821
00:44:34,438 --> 00:44:36,509
It's pointless arguing with him.
跟他说就是对牛弹琴

822
00:44:36,874 --> 00:44:38,251
Drink up. Let's Boo-Boo.
干了这杯 我们走人

823
00:44:44,682 --> 00:44:46,286
We're just five friends
我们只是五个朋友

824
00:44:47,118 --> 00:44:49,223
on a night out, having a good time.
晚上出来逛逛 找些乐子

825
00:45:52,250 --> 00:45:53,750
- Drinking.  - Ah!
- 喝酒  - 啊!

826
00:45:53,751 --> 00:45:55,151
- Beer.  - Pubs.
- 啤酒  - 酒吧

827
00:45:55,152 --> 00:45:56,426
Shall we?
下一家?

828
00:46:01,559 --> 00:46:03,994
I feel a little uncomfortable drinking this much.
喝这么多 我觉得有点不舒服

829
00:46:03,995 --> 00:46:06,029
It's like Dutch courage, isn't it?
酒壮怂人胆 不是吗?

830
00:46:06,030 --> 00:46:08,798
You know, when the English soldiers used to drink Dutch gin before battle
以前英国士兵经常杀敌之前喝荷兰的金酒

831
00:46:08,799 --> 00:46:10,200
to give them super strength.
这会给他们非凡的勇气

832
00:46:10,201 --> 00:46:12,736
You know, I thought that was to numb the sense of impending doom.
我觉得 那是为了削弱害怕的负面影响

833
00:46:12,737 --> 00:46:13,837
Exactly.
完全正确

834
00:46:13,838 --> 00:46:16,876
We're just five friends on a night out, having a good time.
我们就是五个好朋友 晚上出来逛逛 找些乐子

835
00:46:38,562 --> 00:46:40,063
I need the toilet.
我要去厕所

836
00:46:40,064 --> 00:46:42,932
- Go on then. You've earned it.  - Huh?
- 去吧 应该的  - 啊?

837
00:46:42,933 --> 00:46:45,106
You're doing really good, Oliver.
你进步很多啊 奥利弗

838
00:46:46,404 --> 00:46:48,907
He didn't make it this far last time. I'm proud of him.
上次他可没这么持久 我为他骄傲

839
00:46:49,273 --> 00:46:51,007
You're enjoying this, aren't you?
你很享受现在 是吗?

840
00:46:51,008 --> 00:46:53,511
Yeah, five guys on a night out, having a great time.
是啊 五个伙计大晚上一起出来 找乐子

841
00:46:53,611 --> 00:46:55,090
Pretending to have a great time.
假装在找乐子

842
00:46:55,246 --> 00:46:56,413
Are you pretending?
你是在装吗?

843
00:46:56,414 --> 00:46:59,115
If we get out of here alive, I'm going to kill you.
如果我们活着出去 我就把你干掉

844
00:46:59,116 --> 00:47:00,784
We're still in the dark, Gary.
别人还蒙在鼓里呢 加里

845
00:47:00,785 --> 00:47:03,391
Yeah, our families could be in danger for all we know.
是啊 我们的家人可能都受到威胁了

846
00:47:03,554 --> 00:47:07,400
I know, my mum could be dead. For reals this time.
我知道 我老妈这次可能真的要死了

847
00:47:08,159 --> 00:47:11,538
- Hey, why don't we just ask somebody?  - Who?
- 嘿 为什么我们不问问其他人呢?  - 问谁啊?

848
00:47:12,596 --> 00:47:15,805
- The Reverend Green. Come on.  - Wait.
- 就问绿圣人 跟上  - 等等

849
00:47:16,200 --> 00:47:17,734
What the fuck are you doing?
你要去干嘛?

850
00:47:17,735 --> 00:47:20,682
I'm going to go and have a little chat with The Reverend Green.
我过去跟绿圣人私下聊聊

851
00:47:21,272 --> 00:47:22,444
You're going to buy drugs?
你是要去买毒品吗?

852
00:47:22,606 --> 00:47:25,917
I am going to go over there and subtly check if that is The Reverend Green
我就过去旁敲侧击地打探一下他是不是绿圣人

853
00:47:26,077 --> 00:47:29,045
and if it is, I can ask him what's going on,
如果是的话 我就能问他怎么回事了

854
00:47:29,046 --> 00:47:30,548
and possibly buy some drugs.
也许顺便买点毒品

855
00:47:30,848 --> 00:47:32,515
But what if he's one of them?
但如果他也是其中一员吗?

856
00:47:32,516 --> 00:47:34,718
No, me and The Reverend had a highly sophisticated code
不可能 我和圣人谈起买大麻的时候

857
00:47:34,719 --> 00:47:36,639
when discussing the purchase of herbal narcotics.
有个很复杂的暗号

858
00:47:36,854 --> 00:47:41,064
If he doesn't understand me, it means he's one of them and I will simply walk away.
如果他不懂的话 那就说明他是其中一员 那我就走开好了

859
00:47:41,425 --> 00:47:42,426
Ah!
啊!

860
00:47:48,599 --> 00:47:51,434
- Have you got any drugs?  - I don't do that anymore, Gary.
- 还有大麻吗?  - 早就不干了 加里

861
00:47:51,435 --> 00:47:53,436
- Do what?  - That.
- 做什么?  - 这暗号

862
00:47:53,437 --> 00:47:54,804
That why you're in a suit, is it?
所以你穿西装打领带了 是吗?

863
00:47:54,805 --> 00:47:56,639
'Cause drug dealing is not good enough for you?
因为贩毒不能满足你了吗?

864
00:47:56,640 --> 00:47:58,808
There are no drug dealers anymore, Gary.
这里没人贩毒了 加里

865
00:47:58,809 --> 00:48:00,710
I've got a proper job in a proper office.
我现在在固定地点 上固定的班

866
00:48:00,711 --> 00:48:03,313
- You had a proper office.  - That was the gents' toilets.
- 你还有固定地点上班  - 那可是男洗手间

867
00:48:03,314 --> 00:48:05,482
Nothing wrong with doing your business in the toilet.
你以前本来就在洗手间干营生

868
00:48:05,483 --> 00:48:08,123
- Look, a lot has changed since you have left.  - I know.
- 听着 你走了之后 很多事情都改变了  - 我知道

869
00:48:08,285 --> 00:48:10,322
- How much do you?  - A little.
- 你知道多少?  - 就一点

870
00:48:10,454 --> 00:48:11,660
How much is a little?
一点是多少?

871
00:48:11,856 --> 00:48:13,790
The town has been taken over by robots full of blue stuff.
镇子被一群蓝墨水机器人给占领了

872
00:48:13,791 --> 00:48:14,958
Shh. Keep your voice down.
嘘 小声点

873
00:48:14,959 --> 00:48:16,326
You don't even know what you're talking about.
你知道自己在说什么吗

874
00:48:16,327 --> 00:48:18,795
- Tell us then.  - Well, they're not robots.
- 那告诉我们  - 他们不是机器人

875
00:48:18,796 --> 00:48:20,730
Do you even know what robot means?
你知道机器人是什么吗?

876
00:48:20,731 --> 00:48:24,474
Course I do. It's like, "Hello, I am a robot."
我当然知道啦 像这样"你好 我是个机器人"

877
00:48:24,635 --> 00:48:28,271
It means slave and believe me, they are not slaves.
是奴隶的意思 而且相信我 他们不是什么奴隶

878
00:48:28,272 --> 00:48:30,473
- Are you their prisoner?  - No, I am very happy.
- 你变成他们的囚犯了?  - 没有 我很开心

879
00:48:30,474 --> 00:48:31,646
Tell your face.
说谎注意表情啊

880
00:48:31,776 --> 00:48:34,010
Hey! What's going on?
嘿! 怎么样了?

881
00:48:34,011 --> 00:48:36,012
The town's been invaded by robots who aren't robots
这个小镇被自称不是机器人的机器人占领了

882
00:48:36,013 --> 00:48:37,924
- and The Rev's their prisoner.  - I am not.
- 他是他们的囚犯  - 我不是

883
00:48:38,449 --> 00:48:40,827
We're leaving first thing. We can get you out of here.
我们马上就走了 我们能帮你逃出去

884
00:48:41,085 --> 00:48:43,987
I'm not going. It's not what you think. This is for all our benefit.
我不会走的 这里也不是你们想的那样 这对我们大家都好

885
00:48:43,988 --> 00:48:47,458
- You've said too much, Trevor.  - Yeah, put a cork in it, Trevor.
- 你说太多了 特拉沃尔  - 对 该停了 特拉沃尔

886
00:48:47,558 --> 00:48:49,826
- I'm just trying to help.  - It's not your place to help.
- 我只是想帮忙  - 这里不该由你来帮忙

887
00:48:49,827 --> 00:48:51,494
They will have everything in hand.
他们最后会知道一切的

888
00:48:51,495 --> 00:48:52,530
Are you guys robots?
你们是机器人吗?

889
00:48:52,696 --> 00:48:56,041
Well, the word robot actually comes from an old Czech word...
机器人这个词实际上起源于一个古老的捷克词语...

890
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:57,645
- robotnik...  - meaning slave.
- 机器...  - 意思是奴隶

891
00:48:57,835 --> 00:48:59,702
- And we are not slaves.  - We are very, very happy.
- 我们不是奴隶  - 我们过得非常非常开心

892
00:48:59,703 --> 00:49:00,909
And not robots.
所以我们不是机器人

893
00:49:01,038 --> 00:49:02,505
Oh, my God, are these guys robots?
天啊 这些人是机器人吗?

894
00:49:02,506 --> 00:49:03,706
Shut up about robots!
别再谈机器人了!

895
00:49:03,707 --> 00:49:05,375
I say we shut up about everything!
我说我们什么都别再谈了!

896
00:49:12,216 --> 00:49:13,354
Trevor.
特拉沃尔

897
00:49:15,686 --> 00:49:18,132
It's your supervisor.
是你的监督人

898
00:49:20,424 --> 00:49:22,961
- Hello, Trevor.  - Hello, sir.
- 你好 特拉沃尔  - 你好 先生

899
00:49:25,129 --> 00:49:26,767
But...
但...

900
00:49:27,665 --> 00:49:29,042
I understand.
我明白

901
00:49:49,954 --> 00:49:51,365
Thanks a bunch.
太感谢你们了

902
00:49:57,628 --> 00:49:59,039
What did I miss?
我错过了什么?

903
00:49:59,163 --> 00:50:01,164
Your friends trying to help.
你的朋友们想帮忙

904
00:50:01,165 --> 00:50:02,439
We don't need your help.
我们不需要你们的帮忙

905
00:50:02,566 --> 00:50:03,874
Well, what should we do?
那我们该做什么?

906
00:50:04,468 --> 00:50:07,608
I suggest you get on your way.
我建议你们该干什么就干什么

907
00:50:09,507 --> 00:50:11,248
I think we should do what he says.
我觉得我们应该听他的

908
00:50:12,076 --> 00:50:13,419
Okay.
好吧

909
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:20,990
双头狗

910
00:50:21,118 --> 00:50:22,324
Here we go.
我们走吧

911
00:50:25,956 --> 00:50:27,790
- Come on!  - Gary.
- 来吧!  - 加里

912
00:50:27,791 --> 00:50:29,192
Gary!
加里!

913
00:50:29,193 --> 00:50:31,361
Let's just get in and out of this one, yeah?
我们进去就马上出来 怎样?

914
00:50:31,362 --> 00:50:33,103
No more making new friends.
不要再交新朋友了

915
00:50:33,831 --> 00:50:37,133
Gentlemen! The prodigal sons return!
先生们! 浪子回归了!

916
00:50:37,134 --> 00:50:40,081
What will it be, one of our guest ales perchance?
要点什么呢 不如来点啤酒?

917
00:50:41,105 --> 00:50:43,873
Might I recommend five pints of Crowning Glory?
我推荐来五杯至高荣耀啤酒 如何?

918
00:50:43,874 --> 00:50:46,910
- Rather fitting, wouldn't you say, Gary?  - What? Sorry. What?
- 非常合适 你觉得呢 加里?  - 什么? 不好意思 你说什么?

919
00:50:46,911 --> 00:50:50,046
It's a delightful brew. Hoppy, nutty, foamy,
精心酿造 口感跳脱 令人迷醉 泡沫丰富

920
00:50:50,047 --> 00:50:53,187
Does it have a surprisingly fruity note that lingers on the tongue?
喝完是不是还会在舌尖留下水果的味道?

921
00:50:53,484 --> 00:50:55,930
You're obviously a connoisseur.
您一看就是个行家

922
00:50:56,120 --> 00:50:57,987
Then you'll already know that it's a rare treat
那您肯定知道能喝到这种啤酒很难得

923
00:50:57,988 --> 00:51:01,991
for rogues, reverends, royalty and all good folks between.
仅供流氓 传教士 皇室成员和其他好人

924
00:51:01,992 --> 00:51:03,626
Five of those, please.
那就来五杯

925
00:51:03,627 --> 00:51:05,573
Welcome home, boys.
欢迎回家 孩子们

926
00:51:09,967 --> 00:51:11,801
I don't remember him being that friendly.
我都不记得他会这么友好

927
00:51:11,802 --> 00:51:14,180
He's obviously one of them.
他显然是他们中的一员

928
00:51:14,305 --> 00:51:15,905
How can he be? He remembered me.
他怎么可能? 他记得我

929
00:51:15,906 --> 00:51:17,373
We don't know what they remember.
我们不知道他们记得什么

930
00:51:17,374 --> 00:51:18,819
Maybe they have selective memories.
可能他们有选择性记忆

931
00:51:18,976 --> 00:51:20,877
Yeah, like what's his name? Me.
没错 就像 他的名字是什么? 我

932
00:51:20,878 --> 00:51:22,812
Maybe he's one of the others. Like The Reverend.
可能他是其他人中的一员 像老圣人

933
00:51:22,813 --> 00:51:24,156
It is very hard to tell, isn't it?
这很难分辨 对吧?

934
00:51:24,281 --> 00:51:26,249
Yeah, I mean, is he one of them or is he one of them?
对 我是说 他是他们中的一个还是他们中的一个?

935
00:51:26,250 --> 00:51:28,084
Wait, wait, which ones are the thems again?
等等 等等 他们是哪个他们?

936
00:51:28,085 --> 00:51:29,359
Well, they're both thems, aren't they?
有两个他们 对吧?

937
00:51:29,486 --> 00:51:30,720
But there's two ways of saying it.
有两种方法来说

938
00:51:30,721 --> 00:51:32,855
Is he one of them or is he one of them?
他是他们中的一个还是他们中的一个?

939
00:51:32,856 --> 00:51:34,157
We need different terms.
我们要用不同的名称

940
00:51:34,158 --> 00:51:38,129
One for the people who aren't robots and one for the robots who aren't robots.
一个指代不是机器人的人 还有一个指代自称不是机器人的机器人

941
00:51:39,330 --> 00:51:44,404
All right, we need to be able to differentiate between them, them and us.
好吧 我们得能区分他们 他们和我们

942
00:51:44,635 --> 00:51:46,436
Yeah, I think the pronouns are really confusing.
对 我觉得代词真的很难区分

943
00:51:46,437 --> 00:51:48,438
Yes. I don't even know what a pronoun is.
对 我甚至都不知道代词是什么意思

944
00:51:48,439 --> 00:51:50,506
It's a word that can function by itself as a noun
代词自身能起到名词的作用

945
00:51:50,507 --> 00:51:52,175
which refers to something else in the discourse.
但在语境中指代其他东西

946
00:51:52,176 --> 00:51:53,519
- I don't get it.  - You just used one.
- 我没听懂它  - 你刚刚就用了一个

947
00:51:53,644 --> 00:51:55,011
- Did I?  - Yeah. "It" is a pronoun.
- 是吗?  - 用了 "它"就是个代词

948
00:51:55,012 --> 00:51:56,045
- What is?  - It.
- 哪个词?  - 它

949
