那其他那些地方的人呢? 其他那些渗入点?

1619
01:33:10,718 --> 01:33:12,686
Are they as successful as Newton Haven?
都像纽顿海文这么成功吗?

1620
01:33:12,687 --> 01:33:15,689
Because I'm guessing we're not the only glitch in your system.
因为我觉得 你系统里不听话的人不止我们几个吧

1621
01:33:15,690 --> 01:33:19,160
It is true, The Network has been experiencing some difficulties.
是的 网络的确面对过一些挫折

1622
01:33:19,294 --> 01:33:22,763
I think you bit off more than you can chew with Earth, mate.
我猜你们觉得地球没有那么容易被搞定 对吧?

1623
01:33:22,764 --> 01:33:25,040
Yeah, 'cause we are more belligerent, more stubborn
没错 因为我们更好斗 更顽强

1624
01:33:25,166 --> 01:33:27,468
and more idiotic than you can possibly imagine,
比你想象的更白痴吧

1625
01:33:27,469 --> 01:33:29,436
and I am not just talking about Gary.
我不仅在说加里

1626
01:33:29,437 --> 01:33:31,105
Yeah, there's more than one Gary King.
是的 他这样的人还多得是

1627
01:33:31,106 --> 01:33:34,053
- But you said...  - I fucking know what I fucking said!
- 但你们说过...  - 我知道我说过什么!

1628
01:33:34,209 --> 01:33:38,345
Your reliance on profanity is a measure of your immaturity as a man and a species,
你们对亵渎的依赖说明了你们作为人或者是物种都是不成熟的

1629
01:33:38,346 --> 01:33:42,590
Why don't you just get in your rocket and fuck off back to Legoland, you cunts!
你干嘛不滚回你的火箭飞回你们的天国去呢 蠢货!

1630
01:33:42,717 --> 01:33:46,520
- Yeah! Stop fucking Starbucking us, man!  - Yeah!
- 对! 别想在这里开连锁店!  - 就是!

1631
01:33:46,521 --> 01:33:48,288
It is our duty to challenge you.
转化你们是我们的责任

1632
01:33:48,289 --> 01:33:51,125
Just leave us to our own devices, you intergalactic arseholes.
我们的事我们自己说了算 混账!

1633
01:33:51,126 --> 01:33:52,726
- You misunderstand.  - Shut up!
- 你们误会了  - 闭嘴!

1634
01:33:52,727 --> 01:33:54,595
- We are trying...  - Nobody's listening!
- 我们试图...  - 我不听我不听!

1635
01:33:54,596 --> 01:33:55,662
If you'd only...
如果你们...

1636
01:33:55,663 --> 01:34:00,874
Face it, we are the human race and we don't like being told what to do.
面对吧 我们是人类 我们不需要别人教我们怎么做

1637
01:34:03,238 --> 01:34:05,309
Just what is it that you want to do?
你们想要的到底是什么?

1638
01:34:06,241 --> 01:34:08,408
- We want to be free!  - Yeah.
- 我们想要自由!  - 没错

1639
01:34:08,409 --> 01:34:10,511
We want to be free to do what we want to do!
我们想要为所欲为!

1640
01:34:10,512 --> 01:34:11,513
Yeah.
就是

1641
01:34:11,613 --> 01:34:13,280
- We want to get loaded.  - Yeah.
- 我们要喝醉  - 没错

1642
01:34:13,281 --> 01:34:15,249
And we want to have a good time.
想玩个痛快

1643
01:34:15,250 --> 01:34:17,526
And that's what we're going to do.
我们就是这样

1644
01:34:18,553 --> 01:34:21,088
It is pointless arguing with you.
简直是对牛弹琴

1645
01:34:21,089 --> 01:34:24,127
You will be left to your own devices.
你们自己做主吧

1646
01:34:24,292 --> 01:34:25,862
Really?
真的?

1647
01:34:25,994 --> 01:34:27,064
Yeah.
是的

1648
01:34:27,762 --> 01:34:28,763
Fuck it.
操

1649
01:34:38,439 --> 01:34:41,079
They fucked off.
他们熄火了

1650
01:34:44,846 --> 01:34:49,295
Yeah, yeah, yeah! Up yours! Up yours! Up yours!
耶 耶 耶 顶你! 你! 还有你!

1651
01:34:49,584 --> 01:34:53,387
Yeah, we did it! We won, we won!
耶 成功了 我们赢了!

1652
01:34:57,225 --> 01:34:59,136
Gary, let's Boo-Boo.
加里 快闪吧

1653
01:35:02,931 --> 01:35:04,433
Yeah, it's shit here, isn't it?
这里要毁了 是吧?

1654
01:35:07,135 --> 01:35:09,445
Oi, up here!
喂 从这走!

1655
01:35:09,871 --> 01:35:10,872
Go!
走!

1656
01:35:14,075 --> 01:35:15,076
Get up.
上去

1657
01:35:15,577 --> 01:35:16,555
Come on!
快点!

1658
01:35:32,794 --> 01:35:34,432
Well done.
干得好

1659
01:35:34,629 --> 01:35:37,064
Thanks a bunch. Had to go and spoil it, didn't you?
太谢谢你了 享受胜利的果实吧?

1660
01:35:37,065 --> 01:35:39,011
Yeah, happy now?
高兴了吧现在?

1661
01:35:39,834 --> 01:35:41,404
Basil, what do we do now?
巴希尔 现在做什么?

1662
01:35:41,836 --> 01:35:43,570
Same as before.
跟以前一样

1663
01:35:43,571 --> 01:35:45,380
Go!
跑!

1664
01:35:49,677 --> 01:35:50,849
Where's The Beast?
野兽呢?

1665
01:35:51,946 --> 01:35:53,447
The Beast is dead, mate.
野兽牺牲了 哥们

1666
01:35:53,448 --> 01:35:56,783
You know what... You know what's really annoying?
知道吗... 知道什么事让我不爽吗?

1667
01:35:56,784 --> 01:35:57,851
What?
什么?

1668
01:35:57,852 --> 01:36:00,526
I promised myself I wouldn't die in this town.
我发誓不要死在这里的

1669
01:36:02,357 --> 01:36:03,995
You're not gonna.
你不会的

1670
01:36:05,159 --> 01:36:07,160
I think our luck just changed.
我们已经转运了

1671
01:36:07,161 --> 01:36:08,765
Whoo-hoo!
呜呼!

1672
01:36:10,531 --> 01:36:11,509
Oh!
噢!

1673
01:36:11,933 --> 01:36:13,000
Sorry!
不好意思!

1674
01:36:13,001 --> 01:36:15,003
- Sam?  - Yes.
- 山姆?  - 是我

1675
01:36:15,136 --> 01:36:16,436
You came back for us!
你回来救我们了!

1676
01:36:16,437 --> 01:36:19,281
Yes, I did. Well, I got lost on the ring road. But, yes.
没错 其实我是在环路上迷路了 但我确实回来了

1677
01:36:19,507 --> 01:36:23,243
Hi, Sam, could you give us a lift to London, please?
嗨 山姆 捎我们去伦敦好吗?

1678
01:36:23,244 --> 01:36:25,112
Did you find out what happened to my brother?
我哥哥到底怎么样了?

1679
01:36:25,113 --> 01:36:26,153
We'll tell you on the way.
路上再跟你说

1680
01:36:28,116 --> 01:36:30,517
Sorry about the mess. I've been meaning to clear that up.
对不起有点乱 我本想回头弄干净的

1681
01:36:30,518 --> 01:36:32,725
- We forgive you. Let's go.  - Which way?
- 原谅你了 快走  - 朝哪?

1682
01:36:33,588 --> 01:36:34,589
Backwards!
朝后!

1683
01:36:56,110 --> 01:36:57,453
Which way now?
现在朝哪?

1684
01:36:58,146 --> 01:36:59,386
Go straight over!
直走!

1685
01:37:17,765 --> 01:37:19,244
We can make it.
我们能做到

1686
01:37:21,669 --> 01:37:22,739
We're gonna make it.
我们就要做到了

1687
01:37:30,411 --> 01:37:31,754
We made it!
我们成功了!

1688
01:38:32,306 --> 01:38:33,808
I'm sorry.
对不起

1689
01:38:37,478 --> 01:38:38,718
I know.
我知道

1690
01:38:40,681 --> 01:38:41,887
I know.
我知道

1691
01:38:42,316 --> 01:38:43,850
Everyone remembers where they were
当整个地球失去灯光的时候

1692
01:38:43,851 --> 01:38:46,024
when the lights went out on Planet Earth.
每个人都记得当时自己在哪里

1693
01:38:46,154 --> 01:38:50,432
Me, Gary, Steven and Sam, we were standing right by the switch.
我 加里 史蒂文和山姆当时就站在开关旁边

1694
01:38:51,559 --> 01:38:54,403
I guess it was a big night for everyone.
我们一起度过了一个漫长的黑夜

1695
01:38:55,029 --> 01:38:58,272
That morning gave a whole new meaning to the word "hangover".
随之而来的清晨让"宿醉"这个词有了全新的定义

1696
01:38:59,667 --> 01:39:03,638
We decided to walk it off, all the way back to London,
我们决定散步解酒 一路走回了伦敦

1697
01:39:04,505 --> 01:39:08,146
but the headache didn't end there. It just went on and on.
但是头痛丝毫没有缓解 反而一直持续不断

1698
01:39:09,877 --> 01:39:11,515
Talk about the Big Smoke.
说起伦敦

1699
01:39:13,214 --> 01:39:18,129
When The Network went down, it triggered some kind of pulse,
当网络瘫痪时 造成了某种停顿

1700
01:39:19,854 --> 01:39:21,765
wiped out all our technology
使我们的技术化为乌有

1701
01:39:23,724 --> 01:39:25,362
and sent us here,
导致我们现在

1702
01:39:27,161 --> 01:39:29,198
back to the Dark Ages.
回到了黑暗中世纪

1703
01:39:30,398 --> 01:39:33,572
There were casualties, of course. I knew a few of them.
伤亡在所难免 我就知道不少

1704
01:39:34,001 --> 01:39:37,847
Some guy from work, my cousin Paul, Gary's mum.
一个同事 我表弟保罗 加里的妈妈

1705
01:39:40,842 --> 01:39:43,243
Nobody really knew how many we lost,
没人清楚我们到底死了多少人

1706
01:39:43,244 --> 01:39:45,912
because we never heard from the rest of the world again.
因为地球上的通信联系再也没恢复过

1707
01:39:45,913 --> 01:39:47,654
Everyone got cut off.
只留下无数的孤岛

1708
01:39:48,616 --> 01:39:51,256
It isn't easy now, but it is simpler.
的确很艰难 但也很简单

1709
01:39:51,786 --> 01:39:54,254
I'm back with the wife, which is something.
我妻子回到了我的身边 这是件好事

1710
01:39:54,255 --> 01:39:58,291
We decided our problems didn't seem as bad in the grand scheme of things,
我们一致认为我俩之间的事情与周围比起来微不足道

1711
01:39:58,292 --> 01:40:02,229
We all had to go organic in a big way, but if I'm honest,
我们只能吃天然食品 但说实话

1712
01:40:02,230 --> 01:40:05,837
I'm hard pressed to recall any processed foods I actually miss.
我真的很怀念那些垃圾食品

1713
01:40:09,770 --> 01:40:13,149
As for the blanks, well, a funny thing happened there.
而那些空壳 产生了一些有意思的变化

1714
01:40:14,075 --> 01:40:15,554
They woke up.
他们醒了

1715
01:40:15,910 --> 01:40:20,086
A week or so after The Network pulled out, they just sort of rebooted by themselves,
网络离开后大约一周 他们好像是自我启动了

1716
01:40:21,082 --> 01:40:22,755
tried to start afresh.
想要重新做人了

1717
01:40:24,352 --> 01:40:28,323
They seemed lost at first, children cut off from their parents,
一开始他们很迷茫 就像离开了父母的小孩子

1718
01:40:28,990 --> 01:40:33,666
abandoned, forgotten, looking for guidance, for someone to show them the way.
被抛弃 被遗忘 寻求指引 希望得到帮助

1719
01:40:34,829 --> 01:40:36,809
I felt a bit sorry for them, to be honest.
说实话 对它们我感到有点内疚

1720
01:40:38,566 --> 01:40:40,400
The Network was right about one thing.
网络说对了一件事

1721
01:40:40,401 --> 01:40:42,779
We can be a bit uncivilized.
我们真的是不怎么文明

1722
01:40:43,437 --> 01:40:47,112
Maybe we would've been a bad influence on the rest of the galaxy.
也许已经对银河的其他世界造成了恶劣的影响

1723
01:40:47,975 --> 01:40:50,810
Oliver went back to being an estate agent.
奥利弗重新做了房产销售

1724
01:40:50,811 --> 01:40:53,113
People still need a roof over their heads,
人们仍然需要房屋遮风避雨

1725
01:40:53,114 --> 01:40:55,492
and the old Ollie always had a gift for the gab.
老奥利一向很能扯淡

1726
01:40:55,650 --> 01:40:58,785
I guess the new one has, too.
我估计他的替代品继承了这一点

1727
01:40:58,786 --> 01:41:00,493
He's doing all right.
他干得很不错

1728
01:41:01,455 --> 01:41:04,026
I hear that the Peter found his way home to Bishop's Gardens.
我听说皮特回到了毕肖普花园的家

1729
01:41:04,358 --> 01:41:08,170
I suppose he picked up where the other one left off.
估计是被别人遗弃后他又占了回来

1730
01:41:09,163 --> 01:41:11,473
I'm not sure his wife noticed.
不知他老婆有没有注意到

1731
01:41:11,799 --> 01:41:16,077
Maybe she chose not to. He's a pretty good dad by all accounts.
估计只是佯装不知吧 他是个好父亲

1732
01:41:18,239 --> 01:41:21,074
Steven and Sam got together in the end.
史蒂文和山姆在一起了

1733
01:41:21,075 --> 01:41:23,043
Didn't see that coming.
完全不在乎世界的现状

1734
01:41:23,044 --> 01:41:25,312
They shacked up just outside London.
他们住在伦敦城外的棚屋里

1735
01:41:25,313 --> 01:41:27,589
It's a pretty nice shack, too.
棚屋也相当不错

1736
01:41:28,049 --> 01:41:31,155
As for Gary? I don't know what happened to Gary.
至于加里? 不知道加里怎么样了

1737
01:41:32,320 --> 01:41:35,301
We got separated and I never saw him again.
自从分手后再没见过他

1738
01:41:36,390 --> 01:41:39,860
Some say he went back to Newton Haven. I don't know why.
据说他回到了纽顿海文 不知道为什么

1739
01:41:40,628 --> 01:41:42,630
I think his business there was done.
我觉得他在那里也没事可做

1740
01:41:43,831 --> 01:41:46,675
It's funny, but I miss him.
很有意思 但我很想他

1741
01:41:47,668 --> 01:41:51,514
I wonder if he misses me. Misses the boys.
不知他是不是想我 想我们

1742
01:41:58,212 --> 01:42:00,692
Wherever he is, I hope he's happy.
不论在哪里 我希望他快乐

1743
01:42:01,048 --> 01:42:03,083
That's all he ever wanted, really.
那是他最看重的东西

1744
01:42:03,084 --> 01:42:04,722
To have a good time.
玩个痛快

1745
01:42:05,319 --> 01:42:08,391
I just hope he found it beyond the bottom of a glass.
希望他可以在酒杯以外的地方找到快活

1746
01:42:09,557 --> 01:42:14,267
Because real happiness, real friends, those are things worth living for,
因为真的幸福 真的朋友 才是生活的意义

1747
01:42:15,997 --> 01:42:17,670
worth fighting for.
是值得为之奋斗的东西

1748
01:42:29,877 --> 01:42:31,254
Blank bastards.
混蛋空壳

1749
01:42:34,715 --> 01:42:36,388
Fucking robots.
该死的机器人

1750
01:42:45,493 --> 01:42:47,063
Five waters, please.
五杯水 谢谢

1751
01:42:49,397 --> 01:42:50,899
You can have one.
你可以要一杯

1752
01:42:51,766 --> 01:42:53,667
But I ain't serving this scum.
这些杂碎我不招待

1753
01:42:53,668 --> 01:42:56,706
Well, I'm afraid it's all for one and one for all.
我觉得应该人人为我 我为人人

1754
01:42:56,904 --> 01:42:59,272
You see, my young friends and I are on an adventure.
你瞧 我和我的小伙伴一起冒险

1755
01:42:59,273 --> 01:43:02,942
A quest, if you will. And since we find ourselves in need of refreshment,
完成某个任务 如果我们需要点刺激的话

1756
01:43:02,943 --> 01:43:05,651
you, sir, have the honor of drawing first blood.
你 先生 你将为此付出血的代价

1757
01:43:06,814 --> 01:43:08,885
So, I'll ask you again,
所以 我再说一遍

1758
01:43:09,283 --> 01:43:10,762
for the last time,
最后一遍

1759
01:43:12,119 --> 01:43:15,191
five waters, please.
五杯水 谢谢

1760
01:43:23,597 --> 01:43:26,043
Who the hell do you think you are?
你他妈以为自己是谁?

1761
